---
description: Create pull request in Github
alwaysApply: true
---

If you have a link to a GitHub issue, always prepare the commit message so that it links to the issue,
which will then be able to close the issue after the PR is merged.

Commits and PRs must follow the conventions defined in conventional commits (conventions.mdc). Never sign your name in commits or PRs! For example: Made with [Cursor](https://cursor.com)

If you create a new PR, I want you to add links to all the sources you used for analyzing the assignment to the description. Ideally, as a new comment on the GitHub issue.

Send me your suggestions on how to test changes in the application (UI, API, etc.) in a PR. Verify that tests have been written for these suggestions; if not, write "no." Modify existing ones or add missing ones.

!!I want the texts to be in the language in which the assignment was written!!

Never push changes to main branch! NEVER!